I86Ex. Ord. No. T112837K. Deficit Control and Productivity Improvement in the Administration of the Federal Government

I21Ex. Ord. No. 12837, Feb. 10, 1993, 58 F.R. 8205, provided:

I21By the authority vested in me as President by the Constitution and the laws of the United States of America, including the Budget and Accounting Act of 1921, as amended (31 U.S.C. 1101 T3et seqK.), and section 301 of title 3, United States Code, and in order to assist in the control of the Federal deficit and improve the administrative productivity of the Federal Government, it is hereby ordered as follows:

I21T4SectionK 1. All executive departments and agencies shall include a separate category for ``administrative expenses'' when submitting their appropriation requests to the Office of Management and Budget (OMB) for fiscal years 1994 through 1997. The Director of OMB (Director), in consultation with the agencies, shall establish and revise as necessary a definition of administrative expenses for the agencies. All questions regarding the definition of administrative expenses shall be resolved by the Director.

