I34G7T2KResults-oriented_not process-oriented; and

I34G7T2KMarket-based_actively promoting, not stifling, innovation and competition.

I21In order to establish and implement Government reform throughout the executive branch, I hereby direct the following:

I211. T3Establish Chief Operating Officers.

I21Each agency head shall designate a Chief Operating Officer, who shall be the senior official with agency-wide authority on behalf of the Secretary or agency head. The Chief Operating Officer, the equivalent of the Deputy Secretary, shall report directly to the agency head and shall be responsible for:

I22(a) implementing the President's and agency head's goals and the agency's mission;

I22(b) providing overall organization management to improve agency performance;

I22(c) assisting the agency head in promoting Government reform, developing strategic plans, and measuring results; and

I22(d) overseeing agency-specific efforts to integrate performance and budgeting, expand competitive sourcing, strengthen their workforce, improve financial management, advance e-government, apply information policy and technology policies, and other Government-wide management reforms.

I212. T3Implement Additional Agency Reforms.

I21Each agency head shall identify and implement additional changes within the agency that will promote the principles of government reform.

I213. T3Establishment of President's Management Council.

I21In order to advise and assist the President in ensuring that Government reform is implemented throughout the executive branch, I hereby establish the President's Management Council (``Council''). The Council shall comprise:

