I89. Definitions; applicability of subchapter

I11(a) In this subchapter_

I12(1) An obligated balance of an appropriation account as of the end of a fiscal year is the amount of unliquidated obligations applicable to the appropriation less amounts collectible as repayments to the appropriation.

I12(2) An unobligated balance is the difference between the obligated balance and the total unexpended balance.

I12(3) A fixed appropriation account is an appropriation account available for obligation for a definite period.

Q04

I11(b) The limitations on the availability for expenditure prescribed in this subchapter apply to all appropriations unless specifically otherwise authorized by a law that specifically_

I12(1) identifies the appropriate account for which the availability for expenditure is to be extended;

I12(2) provides that such account shall be available for recording, adjusting, and liquidating obligations properly chargeable to that account; and

I12(3) extends the availability for expenditure of the obligated balances.

Q04

I11(c) This subchapter does not apply to_

I12(1) appropriations for the District of Columbia government; or

I12(2) appropriations to be disbursed by the Secretary of the Senate or the Chief Administrative Officer of the House of Representatives.

