I89. Custodians of money

I11(a) Except as provided by another law, an official or agent of the United States Government having custody or possession of public money shall keep the money safe without_

I12(1) lending the money;

I12(2) using the money;

I12(3) depositing the money in a bank; and

I12(4) exchanging the money for other amounts.

Q04

I11(b) Except as provided in section 3718(b)ÿ1A\1\N of this title, an official or agent of the Government receiving money for the Government from any source shall deposit the money in the Treasury as soon as practicable without deduction for any charge or claim.

