I21Pub. L. 99ÿ09509, title VI, subtitle B (ÿ1A6101ÿ096104), ÿ1A6102, Oct. 21, 1986, 100 Stat. 1934, provided that:

I21``(a) T4FindingsK._The Congress finds that_

I22``(1) false, fictitious, and fraudulent claims and statements in Government programs are a serious problem;

I22``(2) false, fictitious, and fraudulent claims and statements in Government programs result in the loss of millions of dollars annually by allowing persons to receive Federal funds to which they are not entitled;

I22``(3) false, fictitious, and fraudulent claims and statements in Government programs undermine the integrity of such programs by allowing ineligible persons to participate in such programs; and

