I89. False claims and statements; liability

I11(a)(1) Any person who makes, presents, or submits, or causes to be made, presented, or submitted, a claim that the person knows or has reason to know_

I12(A) is false, fictitious, or fraudulent;

I12(B) includes or is supported by any written statement which asserts a material fact which is false, fictitious, or fraudulent;

I12(C) includes or is supported by any written statement that_

I13(i) omits a material fact;

I13(ii) is false, fictitious, or fraudulent as a result of such omission; and

I13(iii) is a statement in which the person making, presenting, or submitting such statement has a duty to include such material fact; or

Q04

I12(D) is for payment for the provision of property or services which the person has not provided as claimed,

Q04

I10shall be subject to, in addition to any other remedy that may be prescribed by law, a civil penalty of not more than $5,000 for each such claim. Except as provided in paragraph (3) of this subsection, such person shall also be subject to an assessment, in lieu of damages sustained by the United States because of such claim, of not more than twice the amount of such claim, or the portion of such claim, which is determined under this chapter to be in violation of the preceding sentence.

I11(2) Any person who makes, presents, or submits, or causes to be made, presented, or submitted, a written statement that_

I12(A) the person knows or has reason to know_

I13(i) asserts a material fact which is false, fictitious, or fraudulent; or

I13(ii)(I) omits a material fact; and

I13(II) is false, fictitious, or fraudulent as a result of such omission;

Q04

I12(B) in the case of a statement described in clause (ii) of subparagraph (A), is a statement in which the person making, presenting, or submitting such statement has a duty to include such material fact; and

I12(C) contains or is accompanied by an express certification or affirmation of the truthfulness and accuracy of the contents of the statement,

Q04

I10shall be subject to, in addition to any other remedy that may be prescribed by law, a civil penalty of not more than $5,000 for each such statement.

I11(3) An assessment shall not be made under the second sentence of paragraph (1) with respect to a claim if payment by the Government has not been made on such claim.

I11(b)(1) Except as provided in paragraphs (2) and (3) of this subsection_

I12(A) a determination under section 3803(a)(2) of this title that there is adequate evidence to believe that a person is liable under subsection (a) of this section; or

I12(B) a determination under section 3803 of this title that a person is liable under subsection (a) of this section,

