I89. Gold clauses and consent to sue

I11(a) In this section_

I12(1) ``gold clause'' means a provision in or related to an obligation alleging to give the obligee a right to require payment in_

I13(A) gold;

I13(B) a particular United States coin or currency; or

I13(C) United States money measured in gold or a particular United States coin or currency.

